Package <Unnamed>

Class Summary
BoxBug A BoxBug traces out a square "box" of a given size.
BoxBugRunner This class runs a world that contains box bugs.
CircleBug CircleBug moves in a circular, or octagonal, pattern
CircleBugRunner This class runs a world that contains circle bugs.
DancingBug DancingBug moves in a "dance routine" by moving the appropriate number of steps before turning a specified amount.
DancingBugRunner This class manages a world full of DancingBugs.
JumperBug JumperBug can jump two spaces at a time, but it can jump only over a rock, a flower, or a blank space and only onto a flower or blank space.
JumperBugColoredRunner2014 Based upon AP(r) Computer Science GridWorld Case Study: Copyright(c) 2005-2006 Cay S.
Lovebug Lovebug acts like a normal Bug but also has a chance of breeding and cloning itself into one or two spaces that are empty or occupied by a flower.
Sandstone Sandstone is a type of rock that erodes over time and then eventually disappears from the grid altogether.
SpiralBug SpiralBug moves in a similar pattern as CircleBug but moves in a spiral.
SpiralBugRunner This class runs a world that contains SpiralBugs.
VenusFlyTrap VenusFlyTrap eats bugs that are in front and behind it.
VenusJumperRunner Based upon AP(r) Computer Science GridWorld Case Study: Copyright(c) 2005-2006 Cay S.
VenusSandstoneLovebugRunner Based upon AP(r) Computer Science GridWorld Case Study: Copyright(c) 2005-2006 Cay S.
ZBug ZBug starts facing east and moves in a z pattern before stopping.
ZBugRunner This class creates a world with ZBugs.
